III. CRUIT is the name of a stringed instrument used of old in scotland and Ireland⁷ which was the same with the Welch crwdd or crwth. For a long time past it has been confined to North Wales, so that the people of that part of the principality have been accustomed to consider it as be- ing exclusively their own, as we learn from the Rev. Mr. EvanEvans’ account of it.
